        h3 Requirements

        p Students are required to have strong foundations on algorithms, databases and software engineering. They are also required to have twitter and github accounts.
        Please #[a(href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfnRkeiSb-t9q-2SM3TP36ZOSkICWBXUw8KTlzVqcJxxPRa6Q/viewform?usp=sf_link") use this form to enter your Twitter and Github handle]
        p Every student is required to complete a series of readings and materials before class. This is not only #[strong required] but also very important, since in class we will assume they were reviewed, discuss them and cover more advanced topics.


        h4 Reading comments
        p #[strong Before every class, students must tweet something they learned from the readings with the hashtag #WebDev and the handle @NUSiliconValley]. The comments should be original, shouldn't repeat what was said before, and demonstrate the proficiency of the required reading.
          p These tweets are going to considered for the class participation grade. Each comment will be rated as follows:
          ul
            li #[strong 2 points]: An interesting and original comment
            li #[strong 1 points]: An interesting comment but that was mentioned before by another student
            li #[strong 0 points]: A non interesting comment

